Insert Image file name type masks are offset somehow
description:
#### Steps to reproduce

1. Open Glaxnimate
2. Insert Image...
3. Select the PNG file name type
4. Select the SVG file name type

#### Result

Actual result: Selecting the PNG file type here causes it to match JPG files, and selecting the SVG file type causes it to match PNG files.

#### Version

macOS 11.4
Glaxnimate 0.4.3-11-g8157dfe

title: Trace crashes on Apple Silicon
description:
#### Steps to reproduce

1. Installed dependencies with Brew
2. Built using slightly modified build steps to find the correct paths
3. Opened it
4. Inserted an image
5. Right clicked on the layer
6. Selected Trace...

#### Result

Expected: Apparently a trace dialog should open?
What really happened: It crashed.

#### Version

macOS 11.4
Glaxnimate 0.4.3-11-g8157dfe

An undo for the auto detect colours would be nice, and/or some way to lock in certain colours so they don't get reselected, eg I want to pick a couple of colours and not have them forgotten because I clicked auto to see what it would pick
